        "METHOD_CHI2_GOF_UNIFORM_TITLE": "ГҸВҮГӮВІ Г—В”Г—ВӘГ—ВҗГ—ВһГ—В” (Г—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВҷГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВӘ Г—В Г—ВҗГ—ВҷГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—ВӘ)",
        "METHOD_CHI2_GOF_UNIFORM_DESC": "Pearson ГҸВҮГӮВІ Г—ВўГ—Вң Г—ВЎГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВһГ—ВҰГ—ВҳГ—В‘Г—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӘ (50 Г—ВӘГ—ВҗГ—ВҷГ—Вқ, 5ГғВ—n Г—ВһГ—В§Г—В•Г—ВһГ—В•Г—ВӘ) Г—В•Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВӨГ—Вҷ Г—ВӘГ—В§Г—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВӘ FDJ (starMax).",
        "METHOD_CHI2_GOF_UNIFORM_SUMMARY": "Pearson ГҸВҮГӮВІ: Г—В Г—ВҰГ—ВӨГ—В” Г—ВһГ—В•Г—Вң Г—ВҰГ—ВҷГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—В” Г—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВҷГ—В“Г—В” (Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ + Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВӨГ—Вҷ Г—ВӣГ—ВңГ—ВңГ—Вҷ FDJ).",
        "METHOD_ENTROPY_NORMALIZED_TITLE": "Г—ВҗГ—В Г—ВҳГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—ВӘ Г—В©Г—ВҗГ—В Г—В•Г—Вҹ (Г—ВһГ—В Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВһГ—ВңГ—ВӘ)",
        "METHOD_ENTROPY_NORMALIZED_DESC": "Г—ВҗГ—В Г—ВҳГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—В” Г—ВҗГ—ВһГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—ВӘ H Г—ВңГ—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—В•Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВһГ—В—Г—В•Г—ВңГ—В§Г—ВӘ Г—В‘ГўВҖВ‘log(K) ГўВҖВ” Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—В–Г—В•Г—ВЁ Г—ВҷГ—В—Г—ВЎГ—ВҷГ—ВӘ Г—ВңГ—ВһГ—В§Г—ВЎГ—ВҷГ—ВһГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—В”Г—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВҷГ—В“.",
        "METHOD_ENTROPY_NORMALIZED_SUMMARY": "Г—ВўГ—В“ Г—ВӣГ—ВһГ—В” Г—В”Г—ВӘГ—В“Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—В”Г—ВҗГ—ВһГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВЎГ—В•Г—ВҳГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВһГ—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВҷГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВӘ (Г—ВҗГ—В Г—ВҳГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—В” Г—ВһГ—В Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВһГ—ВңГ—ВӘ).",
        "METHOD_GAP_RECURRENCE_TITLE": "Г—ВһГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—В•Г—В—Г—Вҷ Г—В”Г—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВўГ—В” Г—В—Г—В•Г—В–Г—ВЁГ—ВӘ Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—В”Г—В’Г—ВЁГ—ВңГ—В•Г—ВӘ",
        "METHOD_GAP_RECURRENCE_DESC": "Г—ВңГ—ВӣГ—Вң Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁ 1ГўВҖВ“50, Г—ВһГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—В•Г—В— Г—ВһГ—ВһГ—В•Г—ВҰГ—Вў Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—ВҗГ—ВҷГ—В Г—В“Г—В§Г—ВЎГ—Вҷ Г—В”Г—В’Г—ВЁГ—ВңГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—В©Г—В‘Г—В”Г—Вҹ Г—В”Г—В•Г—Вҗ Г—ВһГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—Вў; Г—ВЎГ—ВҷГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—В—Г—В•Г—В–Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ.",
        "METHOD_GAP_RECURRENCE_SUMMARY": "Г—ВһГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—В•Г—В— Г—ВһГ—ВһГ—В•Г—ВҰГ—Вў Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—В©Г—ВӘГ—Вҷ Г—В”Г—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВўГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВЁГ—ВҰГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—В©Г—Вң Г—ВҗГ—В•Г—ВӘГ—В• Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁ Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—Вҷ.",
        "METHOD_SUM_CORRELATION_TITLE": "Г—ВһГ—ВӘГ—ВҗГ—Вқ ГҺВЈ Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ / ГҺВЈ Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ",
        "METHOD_SUM_CORRELATION_DESC": "Pearson r Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—ВЎГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—В—Г—ВһГ—В©Г—ВӘ Г—В”Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—В”Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВЎГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—В©Г—В Г—Вҷ Г—В”Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—В‘Г—В”Г—В’Г—ВЁГ—ВңГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВўГ—Вқ Г—ВҳГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВЎ Г—ВһГ—ВңГ—Вҗ Г—ВӘГ—В§Г—ВЈ.",
        "METHOD_SUM_CORRELATION_SUMMARY": "Г—В§Г—В©Г—ВЁ Г—ВңГ—ВҷГ—В Г—ВҷГ—ВҗГ—ВЁГ—Вҷ Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—ВЎГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВЎГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—Вқ Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—Вқ (Г—ВһГ—ВӘГ—ВҗГ—Вқ Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—ВЎГ—В•Г—Вҹ).",
        "METHOD_MONTE_CARLO_MAXFREQ_TITLE": "Г—ВӣГ—ВҷГ—В•Г—Вң Monte Carlo Г—ВңГ—ВӘГ—В“Г—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВһГ—ВЁГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—ВӘ",
        "METHOD_MONTE_CARLO_MAXFREQ_DESC": "Г—ВһГ—В©Г—В•Г—В•Г—В” Г—ВӘГ—В“Г—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВһГ—ВЁГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—ВӘ Г—В Г—ВҰГ—ВӨГ—ВӘ Г—В‘Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВңГ—ВЎГ—ВҷГ—ВһГ—В•Г—ВңГ—ВҰГ—ВҷГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВҷГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВӘ Г—В‘Г—ВңГ—Вҷ Г—В”Г—В—Г—В–Г—ВЁГ—В”; Г—ВўГ—ВЁГ—ВҡГўВҖВ‘p Г—ВҗГ—ВһГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—Вҷ.",
        "METHOD_MONTE_CARLO_MAXFREQ_SUMMARY": "Г—В”Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁ Г—В”Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—Вҷ Г—В”Г—ВӘГ—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВЈ Г—В‘Г—ВҷГ—В•Г—ВӘГ—ВЁ Г—ВһГ—В•Г—Вң Г—ВЎГ—ВҷГ—ВһГ—В•Г—ВңГ—ВҰГ—ВҷГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВҗГ—В§Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—ВҷГ—В•Г—ВӘ (Г—ВўГ—ВЁГ—ВҡГўВҖВ‘p Г—ВҗГ—ВһГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—Вҷ).",
        "METHOD_CHI2_GOF_UNIFORM_AI_SPEC": "BINDING METHOD (user choice: ГҸВҮГӮВІ naГғВҜve uniform). Scope = JSON `sinceInclusive` / `tail` / `periods` only. (1) Main balls 1ГўВҖВ“50: let n = number of draws in scope, total slots = 5n. For each kГўВҲВҲ{1,ГўВҖВҰ,50}, count O_k = appearances of k across all five positions of all draws (order within a draw irrelevant). Expected E = 5n/50 each. Pearson ГҸВҮГӮВІ_main = ГҺВЈ_k (O_kГўВҲВ’E)ГӮВІ/E with df = 49. Use PatTool pre-counts in `periods[].mf` / `chi2MainNaive` as cross-check but recompute from `tail` if you show detail. (2) Stars by FDJ era: assign each draw to period P1/P2/P3 using `periodCuts` and JSON `periods[]` starMax (9 / 11 / 12). Within period j with n_j draws and starMax S_j, pool 2n_j star-slots; counts O_s for sГўВҲВҲ{1,ГўВҖВҰ,S_j}; expected E_j = 2n_j/S_j each; ГҸВҮГӮВІ_stars,j = ГҺВЈ_s (O_sГўВҲВ’E_j)ГӮВІ/E_j with df = S_jГўВҲВ’1. State hypotheses explicitly (uniform marginal over slots within era). Do not replace this by generic multinomial-without-replacement theory unless clearly labeled extra; primary deliverable = these ГҸВҮГӮВІ statistics + df + plain interpretation.",
        "METHOD_ENTROPY_NORMALIZED_AI_SPEC": "BINDING METHOD (user choice: normalized Shannon entropy). Scope = draws in `tail` aligned with `periods`. Natural log. (1) Mains: empirical p_k = (count of ball k in pooled 5n slots)/(5n), k=1..50. H_main = ГўВҲВ’ГҺВЈ p_k ln p_k (0 ln 0 = 0). H_norm_main = H_main / ln(50) ГўВҲВҲ [0,1]; equals 1 iff uniform on categories. (2) Stars per era j: categories 1..S_j, total slots 2n_j, same formula H_j; H_norm_j = H_j / ln(S_j). Report numeric H and H_norm; interpret as deviation from max-entropy baseline; optional comparison to uniform benchmark.",
        "METHOD_GAP_RECURRENCE_AI_SPEC": "BINDING METHOD (user choice: inter-draw recurrence gaps). Index draws in chronological order as `tail` (index t=0..nГўВҲВ’1). For each ball bГўВҲВҲ{1,ГўВҖВҰ,50}, list indices T_b where b appears (ГўВүВӨ1 per draw). If |T_b|ГўВүВҘ2, gaps ГҺВ”_i = T_b[i]ГўВҲВ’T_b[iГўВҲВ’1]; mean gap ГЎВёВЎ_b = mean(ГҺВ”). Summarize over balls with ГўВүВҘ2 appearances: e.g. mean of ГЎВёВЎ_b, spread (sd/min/max). Descriptive only; links to renewal/inter-arrival intuition allowed but no forecast claim. Ignore balls with <2 hits for ГЎВёВЎ_b.",
        "METHOD_SUM_CORRELATION_AI_SPEC": "BINDING METHOD (user choice: Pearson correlation of sums). Consider draws where there are exactly five main integers in [1,50] and two star integers in [1,starMax] for that drawГўВҖВҷs regulatory era (derive starMax from date vs `periodCuts`). Let X = sum of five mains, Y = sum of two stars. Pearson r between X and Y across all qualifying draws; report sample size n_used. State formula r = cov(X,Y)/(ГҸВғ_X ГҸВғ_Y). No causal interpretation; mention linear association only.",
        "METHOD_MONTE_CARLO_MAXFREQ_AI_SPEC": "BINDING METHOD (user choice: Monte Carlo calibration of max pooled frequency). From `tail`, pooled main counts over 5n slots; M_obs = max_{k=1..50} count(k). Null operational model for simulation: independent draws, each draw picks 5 distinct mains uniformly from {1,ГўВҖВҰ,50} without replacement across drawsГўВҖВҷ sampling mechanism is approximated by repeating n independent such draws; replicate RГўВүВҘ800 times; each replicate yields M_sim; empirical one-sided p-value = (#(M_sim ГўВүВҘ M_obs)+1)/(R+1). State R and that procedure; if you vary R, say so. Not a proof of biasГўВҖВ”interpret as descriptive Monte Carlo tail probability.",
        "AI_SELECTED_METHOD_HINT": "**Normative methodology:** The user selected **`{{label}}`** (`{{id}}`). You MUST treat **`calculationMethodSpec`** in the JSON as the **binding operational definition** of that choice (not just the short summary). Apply it step-by-step when reasoning on `tail` / `periods`. Quick reminder: {{summary}} ГўВҖВ” Data: all draws since `sinceInclusive` appear in `tail` (`tail.length` = `c`); aggregates in `periods`. Echo fields `calculationMethodId`, `calculationMethodLabel`, `calculationMethodSummary` only as labels; **`calculationMethodSpec` overrides ambiguity.**",
        "AI_FAB_TOOLTIP": "**EuroMillions**: Г—В”Г—В Г—В—Г—ВҷГ—В” + JSON `pat-eurom-ai-v2` (Г—ВҰГ—В‘Г—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—ВӘ + **Г—ВӣГ—Вң** Г—В”Г—В”Г—В’Г—ВЁГ—ВңГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВһГ–Вҫ{{since}} Г—В‘Г–Вҫ`tail`). Г—В©Г—ВңГ—ВҷГ—В—Г—В” Г—ВҷГ—В“Г—В Г—ВҷГ—ВӘ.",
        "AI_PROMPT_FROM_SCRATCH": "**EuroMillions ГўВҖВ” human-readable answer.** Data = **`pat-eurom-ai-v2`** below (PatTool pre-counts): scope **`sinceInclusive` = {{since}}** (server property `euromillions.ai.min-draw-date`); **`c`={{n}}** draws in that scope; **`periods[]`** per era (`mf` for mains **1ГўВҖВ“50** across **5ГғВ—n** slots, `sf` for stars up to **starMax**, **`chi2*Naive`**), plus **`tail`** = **every** draw in that scope, chronological tuples `[YYYYMMDD,[5 mains],[ГўВҳВ…,ГўВҳВ…]]` (**`tail.length`** = **`c`**).** Mandatory order:** **(1) Lead with grids ГўВҖВ” zero preamble:** first printable lines must be **GRID_A:** one line, **five ascending mains + two ascending stars**, plain language e.g. `Main balls: 7, 12, 23, 34, 45 ГўВҖВ” Stars: 3, 9`. Then **GRID_B:** second deterministic line, same pattern. Then **one sentence**: these are **statistical model outputs from the JSON**, not the official next draw. **(2) Short method ГўВҖВ” max five bullet lines**, each one short sentence (**no** extra sections or long prose). **Forbidden:** dumping rows like `PГўВҖВҰ ball s=ГўВҖВҰ obs=ГўВҖВҰ smoothed_prob=` for dozens of indices (fills the reply and truncates before the user sees numbers). At most **one** ГҸВҮГӮВІ + **df** line if helpful. **(3) Fair play ГўВҖВ” one sentence:** draws are random; no prophecy.** Presentation:** PatTool renders **Markdown** (`##` / `###`, **bold**, bullets, horizontal rules, blockquotes for colour/tint in the UI). Structure the answer that way; **no** raw HTML/`style=`. A **small** GFM table (header + **only** **GRID_A**/**GRID_B** rows) is fine; **no** huge tables.** Always forbidden:** long numeric traces **before** GRID_A; decorative RNG.",
        "AI_MULTI_METHOD_HINT": "**Multiple methodologies:** If JSON contains **`calculationMethods`** (array), root fields (`calculationMethodId`, `calculationMethodSpec`, ГўВҖВҰ) duplicate the **primary** lens (**`{{primaryLabel}}`**, id **`{{primaryId}}`**). You MUST honor **every** rowГўВҖВҷs **`calculationMethodSpec`** when commenting on `tail` / `periods`. Tie angles briefly (**{{labels}}**) **without** merging incompatible statistical definitions into one vague paragraph; note tensions honestly.",
        "AI_MULTI_SYNTHESIS_HINT": "**Multi-method synthesis mode:** **`calculationMethods`** lists **`{{n}}`** binding specs (UI order). Run **each** method **only inside its own subsection** per the main prompt **before** cross-method synthesis. Do **not** blur distinct operational definitions; **`{{primaryLabel}}`** (`{{primaryId}}`) anchors GRID reasoning continuity with root duplicate fields.",
        "AI_PROMPT_MULTI_SYNTHESIS": "**EuroMillions ГўВҖВ” multi-method synthesis (human-readable).** Same data schema **`pat-eurom-ai-v2`** as standard scratch: **`sinceInclusive` = {{since}}**, **`c`={{n}}**, **`periods[]`**, **`tail`** (**`tail.length`** = **`c`**).** Mandatory order:** **(1) Grids first ГўВҖВ” zero preamble:** **GRID_A** then **GRID_B** as in standard scratch (five ascending mains + two ascending stars each line); one sentence that these are **model outputs**, not the official draw. **(2) Per-method blocks:** For **each** object in JSON **`calculationMethods`** (preserve order), add **`###`** heading = that rowГўВҖВҷs **`calculationMethodLabel`**, then **max three** `-` bullets applying **only** that rowГўВҖВҷs **`calculationMethodSpec`** to `tail`/`periods`. One subsection per method; **no** mixing formulas across subsections. If **`calculationMethods`** is absent (single-method payload), treat root **`calculationMethodSpec`** as the only block (still use **`###`** + three bullets max). **(3) Cross-method synthesis:** `## Cross-method synthesis` then **3ГўВҖВ“5** `-` bullets on agreements, caveats, or non-reconcilable tension (**without** forcing a false reconciliation); **one** cautious sentence: none of this predicts the official draw. **(4) Fair play ГўВҖВ” one sentence.** Same Markdown/HTML rules as standard scratch (**no** raw HTML/`style=`).",
        "AI_STATS_PAYLOAD_INTRO": "**Attached JSON (`pat-eurom-ai-v2`)** ГўВҖВ” scope **`sinceInclusive`** (**{{since}}**): use `periods` + `tail` (**full** chronological list for that window; **`tail.length`** = **`c`**).",
        "AI_JSON_BLOCK_INTRO": "JSON Г—В“Г—В—Г—В•Г—ВЎ (Г—ВӨГ—В—Г—В•Г—ВӘ Г—ВҳГ—В•Г—В§Г—В Г—ВҷГ—Вқ): `c` = **Г—ВЎГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В” Г—ВЎГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВӘ** = **`d.length`**. Г—ВӣГ—Вң `d[i]` = `[ \"YYYYMMDD\", [5 Г—ВӣГ—В“Г—В•Г—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вқ Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В©Г—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вқ], [Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘1, Г—ВӣГ—В•Г—ВӣГ—В‘2] ]` Г—ВӣГ—ВЁГ—В•Г—В Г—В•Г—ВңГ—В•Г—В’Г—Вҷ.",
        "AI_RECORD_COUNT_LINE": "Г—ВЎГ—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВЁГ—В” **Г—ВЎГ—В•Г—ВӨГ—ВҷГ—ВӘ**: **{{n}}** (= Г—В©Г—В“Г—В” JSON `c`; Г—ВҰГ—ВЁГ—ВҷГ—Вҡ Г—ВңГ—В”Г—ВҷГ—В•Г—ВӘ Г—В©Г—В•Г—В•Г—В” Г—ВңГ–Вҫ**`tail.length`** Г—В‘Г—ВЎГ—ВӣГ—ВһГ—В” Г—В–Г—В•). Г—ВҗГ—Вқ Г—В”Г—В”Г—В§Г—В©Г—ВЁ Г—В Г—ВЁГ—ВҗГ—В” Г—В—Г—ВӘГ—В•Г—Вҡ ГўВҖВ” Г—ВҰГ—ВҷГ—ВҷГ—Вҹ Г—В–Г—ВҗГ—ВӘ; Г—ВҗГ—В—Г—ВЁГ—ВӘ **`c`** Г—В•Г–Вҫ**`tail.length`** Г—ВӘГ—В•Г—ВҗГ—ВһГ—ВҷГ—Вқ.",
        "AI_MESSAGE_1": "EuroMillions draws in **compact** JSON below. Trust **`c`** and the bold line; use visible `d` tuples. If context is partial, say so. First apply **state-of-the-art statistics & probability** on the visible history: empirical laws & dependence structure for mains + stars if testable; entropy/gaps/ranks; **GOF**, **bootstrap/permutation**, **multiplicity-aware** inference; regime changes if periods differ combinatorially. **Show your work**: for every major step give **reproducible calculation detail**ГўВҖВ”named hypotheses, explicit formulas, tabulated or summarised counts from the data you see, test statistics and **p**-values / CIs (or bootstrap/permutation bands), model hyperparameters, and the exact optimisation or selection rule + objective value that yields each slip. **Then**, compulsory final section (e.g. ГўВҖВңModel-derived play slipsГўВҖВқ), output **ГўВүВҘ2 full candidate combinations** (5 mains + 2 stars) constructed **deterministically** from that pipelineГўВҖВ”each combination must trace back to those computations (**no** black-box picks). Briefly quantify under your model vs i.i.d. uniform if tractable; one sentence: fair-draw physics means claims of **edge** versus true randomness are usually unwarrantedГўВҖВ”deliver slips as **explicit outputs** of your estimators nevertheless.",
